Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.44,0:00:18.46,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.70,0:00:29.88,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.12,0:00:36.84,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.08,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.18,0:00:56.90,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.15,0:01:08.78,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.03,0:01:20.68,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.92,0:01:26.53,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.77,0:01:36.32,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.70,0:00:29.88,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.12,0:00:36.84,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.08,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.18,0:00:56.90,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.15,0:01:08.78,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.03,0:01:20.68,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.92,0:01:26.53,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.77,0:01:36.32,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.35,0:01:49.24,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 08 - The Eve of our Departure
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.58,0:02:02.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.39,0:02:06.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,By the time we noticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.26,0:02:11.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,brother was already swept away all the way out\Ninto the open sea, clutching onto a barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.80,0:02:14.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:16.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta hurry up and help Ben!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.59,0:02:19.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go save him in that boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:20.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how to row?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.65,0:02:22.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't, but Billy must know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.89,0:02:24.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry girls, but I got nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.71,0:02:26.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.63,0:02:29.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just a bit more...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.70,0:02:36.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Guess we've no choice,\Nbut to ask those guys for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.42,0:02:37.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're thoroughly drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.80,0:02:40.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, this boat belongs to them, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.50,0:02:50.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My brother needs help! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.11,0:02:55.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, we tol' him not to go, dint we?\NThat kid just went to fetch the barrel all by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.70,0:03:00.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that,\Nbut I'm asking you to help him now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.46,0:03:02.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just row the boat for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.15,0:03:07.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're in no condition to do any'ing now.\NAin't that obvious? I'm feeling sleepy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.88,0:03:11.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey mister! We helped push your cart before, innit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.25,0:03:13.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You could at least row the boat in exchange!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.33,0:03:16.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad, kids, but I don't know a thing\Nabout rowing boats.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.19,0:03:22.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we also won't help\Nany of you ever again, understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.48,0:03:23.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.79,0:03:26.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't he just let go of the damn barrel\Nand swim back on his own?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.94,0:03:29.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I told him we don't need that kinda barrel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.57,0:03:31.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben looks exhausted already!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.02,0:03:34.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:36.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.19,0:03:39.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:46.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't nothing we can accomplish\Nwith grown-ups who are so drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:48.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But Ben...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.32,0:03:49.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I will row the boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.64,0:03:50.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really, Billy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:52.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try something, at least!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.02,0:03:56.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Way to go, kid! That's what a proper boy oughta be like!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.40,0:03:59.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And... here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:10.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He drifted further away into the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.70,0:04:11.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lend us a hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.18,0:04:20.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.29,0:04:33.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No need. Kate, you just wait here.\NI'll try rowing it by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.56,0:04:36.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think we'll go faster if we both use 1 oar at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.48,0:04:37.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:40.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Be a good girl and wait here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.68,0:04:42.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Billy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:58.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?\NBen is over there! Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:00.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We know that! Stop yelling!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.58,0:05:03.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right! It's moving now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.28,0:05:04.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up, Billy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.62,0:05:08.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, those kids are rowing your boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.62,0:05:10.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they don't capsize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.55,0:05:15.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?\NWe haven't advanced an inch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.82,0:05:17.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.75,0:05:18.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.78,0:05:21.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Umf!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.68,0:05:35.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That would be the last one\Nof your things, Mr. Popple!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.72,0:05:38.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you! You've helped us a great deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.30,0:05:40.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Very well! Take care and farewell!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.69,0:05:44.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple, are you sure you want to leave\Nthat prefabricated home behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.67,0:05:47.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Mr. Pettywell will later come pick it up himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.88,0:05:48.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:50.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You sold it to that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.02,0:05:51.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to have a surplus of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:56.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And the one who is the most interested\Nin that prefabricated home is Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.46,0:05:59.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather you not sell it to someone so ill-tempered.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.25,0:06:02.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I also wasn't even considering\Nselling it to him at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.60,0:06:06.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But in the end, he was the one\Nwho offered the best price for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:08.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.48,0:06:09.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.20,0:06:12.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.78,0:06:16.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see it? Something like a barrel\Nis floating over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.98,0:06:18.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.27,0:06:20.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And there's also someone clutching onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:21.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.41,0:06:24.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.07,0:06:26.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Should we get closer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:27.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.09,0:06:36.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Ben!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:40.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! It really is Ben!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.16,0:06:41.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ben!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.28,0:06:43.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.18,0:06:46.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing all the way out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.30,0:06:49.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you to look after our belongings, Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:50.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.81,0:07:00.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This kind of rowing won't get us anywhere!\NWe're only getting drenched this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.85,0:07:03.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's you who has the sloppiest rowing here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.25,0:07:05.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you say so, just lemme row alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.17,0:07:07.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. If you say so, do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.73,0:07:21.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like you don't know what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:26.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do? I haven't rowed a boat\Neven once up until now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.34,0:07:28.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:36.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see Ben anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.16,0:07:38.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.28,0:07:42.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did he drown?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.60,0:07:48.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get so worked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.21,0:07:51.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It must be that he's been saved by that boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.13,0:08:18.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.09,0:08:23.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mr. Jamling? Is your leg doing fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.66,0:08:26.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can more or less say so.\NAs you can see, I can walk now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.04,0:08:29.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be best if you don't strain yourself too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.21,0:08:32.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, your husband hadn't returned yet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.85,0:08:36.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He went to unload\Nour remaining things from the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.69,0:08:43.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's been decided that we move\Nto Adelaide tomorrow, with all of our things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.46,0:08:50.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I already knew that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.51,0:08:55.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true that Mr. Popple sold\Nthe prefabricated home to Mr. Pettywell?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.50,0:08:57.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? To Mr. Pettywell?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.78,0:08:58.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.00,0:09:00.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I heard about it from Mr. Parker.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:02.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, he was also vying for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:06.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I was told Mr. Parker\Noffered to buy it for a good price...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.89,0:09:08.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To me, it's straight-up outrageous!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.91,0:09:13.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell was also the man who snatched\Nan oxcart your husband was planning to hire!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.09,0:09:15.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks he can get whatever he wants with money!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.44,0:09:17.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why sell your home to him, of all people?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.81,0:09:19.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those materials were very heavy and bulky.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:24.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My husband judged that transporting them to Adelaide\Nwould be more trouble than what it's worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.79,0:09:28.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that oxen and horses strong enough\Nto transport things are sparse in this place...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.09,0:09:33.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, we have no choice but to bring in\Nmore oxen and horses from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.40,0:09:34.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.69,0:09:39.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But eventually, didn't Mr. Popple manage\Nto find a good oxcart for tomorrow's moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.51,0:09:42.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If only Mr. Pettywell\Ndidn't snatch the oxcart he was originally...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.22,0:09:53.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Madam. Your husband's not back yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.10,0:09:56.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's gone to the ship, Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:10:00.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see. I was also going to the ship now,\Nso maybe I'll run into him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.09,0:10:02.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.88,0:10:10.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Madam, don't hold a grudge against me, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.98,0:10:16.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mind you, I paid quite the fortune\Nfor that prefabricated home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.11,0:10:17.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not holding any grudges...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.83,0:10:19.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? In that case, sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.52,0:10:23.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then, it's about time\Nwe unload my prefabricated home from the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.25,0:10:32.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What a disagreeable man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.62,0:10:54.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem like Bard\Nis going to wake up any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.83,0:10:57.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he does, will he be able to speak right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.16,0:10:59.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... If he's {\i1}that{\i0} drunk, we're in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.45,0:11:04.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea this mister was also the one\Nwho's supposed to transport our stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.18,0:11:07.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, isn't there anyone else you could ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.01,0:11:11.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I told you yesterday. Mr. Bard's oxcart\Nwas the only one vacant around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:15.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're short of oxen and horses,\Nable to pull the cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.52,0:11:18.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the way it is.\NImmigrants keep coming one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.91,0:11:21.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And so, everyone just dumps their stuff\Nhere, on the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.56,0:11:24.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They have no other means\Nof transporting it to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.99,0:11:28.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The shortest way from here to Adelaide\Nis still over 10 kilometers long.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:29.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:33.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We have no other choice,\Nbut to have Mr. Bard transport our things, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.87,0:11:37.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If we don't do that, there's no telling\Nwhen we'll have another chance to move there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:41.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bard seems extremely unlikely to wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.65,0:11:43.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:47.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, we'll have wait for him\Nto wake up, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:51.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We shouldn't load our things\Non his cart without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.74,0:12:00.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:16.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.86,0:12:17.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.15,0:12:20.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.66,0:12:23.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John, you shouldn't have startled me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.89,0:12:25.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I'll refill it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.82,0:12:29.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They gave you a furlough?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.18,0:12:32.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was helping your father get his luggage ashore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.98,0:12:35.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In just half an hour more,\NI'm expected back on the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.45,0:12:36.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Half an hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.46,0:12:43.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll have to part tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:44.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I intend to keep my promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:49.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'll take you little brother\Nand return to our southern Australia later?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.37,0:12:51.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't seem to believe it still.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.94,0:12:54.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.00,0:12:57.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.71,0:13:00.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This distance between here and England\Nis so unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.81,0:13:02.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It takes 100 days to cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.94,0:13:05.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your resolve will definitely fade in that long a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.04,0:13:10.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me and my brother will migrate\Nto southern Australia together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:13.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no revoking this decision, come what may.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.03,0:13:16.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what if your little brother refuses?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.08,0:13:20.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The lad is still just a small kid, and because we've\Nno parents, I am his only guardian.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:24.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Brother will listen to whatever I tell him to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.40,0:13:26.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll meet again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.20,0:13:28.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.49,0:13:30.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And tomorrow we're not parting\Nfor the rest of our lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.38,0:13:32.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.08,0:13:36.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.94,0:13:38.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:42.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.79,0:13:43.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.36,0:13:45.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting in such a place!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.01,0:13:46.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,W-What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.97,0:13:50.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This creature my sister Lucy-May\Nhas been looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.60,0:13:52.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.85,0:13:54.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, at that tree's branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.97,0:13:57.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.87,0:13:59.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.49,0:14:01.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look. Look, over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.92,0:14:03.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! There it is! There!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:06.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A bear cub?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.38,0:14:08.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They say it's called a koala.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.88,0:14:10.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Cute thing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.41,0:14:14.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.43,0:14:15.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.22,0:14:16.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Catch the koala.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.46,0:14:17.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.68,0:14:22.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I mean... It's sitting so high up. And besides,\Nthe branches around that place are all thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.84,0:14:25.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May is crazy about getting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:26.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.07,0:14:28.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.87,0:14:31.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You want it no matter what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.18,0:14:32.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.61,0:14:35.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Then, I'll catch it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.21,0:14:49.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.72,0:14:51.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Leave this to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.78,0:15:04.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Only one last push!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.47,0:15:06.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.57,0:15:07.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.57,0:15:09.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This guy won't bite me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.06,0:15:11.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.12,0:15:14.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know for sure, but I was told it's peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.10,0:15:18.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it! One last push!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.12,0:15:20.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.29,0:15:29.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! That hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.83,0:15:31.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That was pretty rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.32,0:15:33.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But look, it's still not trying to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.47,0:15:34.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please try once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:35.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.50,0:15:36.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.32,0:15:37.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My time is up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.80,0:15:38.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.99,0:15:40.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I really have no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.90,0:15:42.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.09,0:15:45.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who should apologize\Nfor making you climb a tree for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.98,0:15:51.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're not very good at climbing trees, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.69,0:15:55.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably, yes. Ever since I was little,\Ntree climbing wasn't my forte.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.29,0:15:57.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, I still struggle with masts...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.19,0:16:00.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was inconsiderate of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.57,0:16:01.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was asking for too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.08,0:16:04.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mention it.\NBut now, it's really time for me to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.91,0:16:08.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to also help you carry the bucket,\Nbut now I have to dash to make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.75,0:16:10.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go, then. Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.28,0:16:14.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:15.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.89,0:16:21.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I believe you, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:26.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow morning, I'll also come to see you off\Nwhen you depart for Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:29.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be asking for too much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.62,0:16:30.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll think of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.79,0:16:53.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, I'm sorry it took so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.10,0:16:54.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You met with John, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.27,0:16:56.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.70,0:16:59.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about Lucy-May? Still away?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:00.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.99,0:17:05.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She said she'll take the goat for grazing,\Nbut I wonder where she's gone off to...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.79,0:17:08.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Speak of the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.11,0:17:11.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.34,0:17:14.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're such bad children, you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.20,0:17:15.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just where have you been for so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.84,0:17:16.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To the shore!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.96,0:17:20.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There, dad and Ben told us\Nthey won't be returning until the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.09,0:17:20.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.97,0:17:25.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To start loading onto the cart our things unloaded from the ship, they'll have to wait until the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.06,0:17:27.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what are those two going to do until then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.25,0:17:30.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben is looking after our belongings,\Nwhile dad went to look for a crate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.95,0:17:31.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A crate?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.75,0:17:33.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A crate in which we'll put Sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:36.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why would we need to put a goat into the box?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.47,0:17:39.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we can't have her\Nwalk all the way to Adelaide, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.29,0:17:41.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So she'll ride the cart, inside a crate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.29,0:17:42.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're bringing the goat along?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.58,0:17:45.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we do! She's my Sticky, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.85,0:17:48.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The goat milk would invariably\Ncome in handy for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.15,0:17:50.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Actually!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.93,0:17:51.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.30,0:17:55.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A little while ago I saw a Koala.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.42,0:17:57.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? A Koala?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.05,0:17:59.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.38,0:18:02.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right by the creek. You know,\Nthis place perfectly suited for gathering water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.97,0:18:05.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But now that koala is no longer there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.40,0:18:08.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was still there by the time I turned back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.36,0:18:11.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, John even tried to catch it for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.62,0:18:14.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait a moment, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.69,0:18:17.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least help us out a bit down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.53,0:18:20.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I swear, those two are hopeless, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.23,0:18:22.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You really could have kept it to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.98,0:18:25.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. What do you need help with?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.15,0:18:27.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.04,0:18:29.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm running a bit low on the firewood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.50,0:18:30.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go gather some more, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.31,0:18:32.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.49,0:18:33.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could it still be there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.93,0:18:35.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}must{\i0} be there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.55,0:18:41.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.24,0:18:45.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.89,0:18:48.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which tree are we looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.94,0:18:53.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.32,0:18:54.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.17,0:18:54.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:18:58.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's really there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.57,0:19:09.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister, you can climb, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.17,0:19:10.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.15,0:19:12.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't climb a tree that high.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.03,0:19:14.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.38,0:19:15.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a no-go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.99,0:19:17.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a no-go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.44,0:19:19.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I want to catch it, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.44,0:19:22.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'd have caught it if only we could climb.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.47,0:19:25.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go get Billy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.08,0:19:27.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a moment, Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.21,0:19:29.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna climb yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.00,0:19:30.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.22,0:19:33.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lucy-May.\NLet's quit our catching mission for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.98,0:19:35.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.11,0:19:37.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you catch it, what would you do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.03,0:19:39.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's obvious. I'll adopt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.87,0:19:43.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.\NYou can't take it with you to Adelaide, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.62,0:19:44.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.78,0:19:48.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't pack the cart\Nwith something so useless to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.50,0:19:51.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I bet, it would be packed full\Nwith just all the stuff we already have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.13,0:19:55.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think dad would allow you\Nto pile an extra koala on top of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.91,0:19:59.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad agreed to take the goat in\Nbecause it can produce milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.88,0:20:01.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But with a koala...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.23,0:20:02.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll carry it myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.80,0:20:07.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But there would definitely be some other luggage\Nfor the two of us to carry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.09,0:20:10.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.50,0:20:27.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure those can be found in Adelaide, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:30.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If they live here, they probably live there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.42,0:21:00.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, there's another ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.66,0:21:15.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It must be that it's carrying\Nsome new immigrants to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:26.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And now, a once-over of tomorrow's procedures.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.55,0:21:31.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, Kate, and Clara, once we finish\Narranging all of our belongings on the cart,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.42,0:21:34.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,you'll take your clothes and other lightweight luggage\Nand depart first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.60,0:21:36.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You mean, we'll go ahead of everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.63,0:21:37.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.31,0:21:39.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The cart would be packed full with furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.54,0:21:43.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, we, with the ox,\Nwould be moving one step at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.40,0:21:46.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You girls would go to Adelaide first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.03,0:21:48.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There, you'll be waiting for our arrival on the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.21,0:21:52.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,However, we'll have no idea\Nwhere to go once we're in Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.59,0:21:54.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You never told us where our house is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.66,0:21:56.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I'll draw a map for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.68,0:22:00.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get there, you'll see\Nthat Adelaide is awfully easy to navigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.49,0:22:04.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You two make sure you endure such a long walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.75,0:22:08.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father said it's no less than 10 kilometers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.42,0:22:10.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Roughly 10 kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.70,0:22:13.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Does our new house\Nhas any features to help us recognize it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.99,0:22:15.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Features?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.67,0:22:18.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The entrance there is decorated\Nwith a red bow-knot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.70,0:22:22.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, why is there a red bow-knot already?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.00,0:22:25.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, a welcoming gift from our neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.60,0:22:28.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, what am I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.83,0:22:33.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get up early tomorrow\Nand bring Mr. Bard, the coachman, to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.47,0:22:36.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably, by tomorrow morning\Nhe'll be sober already.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.41,0:22:38.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.18,0:22:44.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Also Ben, tomorrow, you might have\Nto stay behind for some while.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.02,0:22:45.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Stay behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.11,0:22:48.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think, we might not be able\Nto load our belongings onto the cart all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.65,0:22:51.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I would ask you to stay behind, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.39,0:22:53.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can't just throw our things away, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.70,0:22:55.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.79,0:22:58.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, would you like to add anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.39,0:23:03.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... Tomorrow is promising to become\Na very long day for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.62,0:23:06.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, let's all go to bed early tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.88,0:23:40.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister, you think there are koalas in Adelaide, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.63,0:23:48.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.32,0:24:07.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The three of us departed for Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.28,0:24:10.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But while on the way,\Nwe meet someone we didn't expect to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.68,0:24:14.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow,\N"The Road to Adelaide".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.30,0:24:15.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
